    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing break statement in get_sf_retxBSRTimer causing unintended fallthrough\n\n### Summary\nThere is a missing break statement in switch case causing unintended fallthrough downstream of function get_sf_retxBSRTimer. When calling get_sf_retxBSRTimer() the behavior is not what is expected. The issue may be in get_sf_retxBSRTimer or a function downstream/upstream of it.\n\nThe function had unreachable break statements after return statements, which while not functionally incorrect, indicated poor code quality. More importantly, the function did not explicitly handle the spare enum values (spare2, spare1) from the RetxBSR-Timer-r12 ASN.1 definition, causing them to fall through to the default case and return -1, which may not be handled properly by calling code.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/ue_procedures.c`: Cleaned up get_sf_retxBSRTimer function by removing unreachable break statements and improving code clarity.\n"
}